cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.PL

The paper deals with abstract argumentation frameworks and proposes a plausibility-based extension semantics for them. This involves using default reasoning and ranking construction paradigm to interpret arguments and attacks by conditional knowledge bases. These concepts are closely related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and logic (cs.LO). The paper also discusses algorithms and properties, which are relevant to computer science theory (cs.CR) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the use of plausibility maximization suggests a connection to programming languages (cs.PL).
